About Hedy Lamarr

Often called "The Most Beautiful Woman in Film," Hedy Lamarr's beauty and screen presence made her one of the most popular actresses of her day.

She was born Hedwig Eva Maria Kiesler on November 9, 1914 in Vienna, Austria. At 17 she appeared in her first film, a German project called Geld auf der Strase. After several European roles, the 1932 film Exstase brought her to the attention of Hollywood producers and she soon signed with MGM.

In Hollywood, Hedy changed her name and starred in Algiers (1938) opposite Charles Boyer. She went on to appear alongside Spencer Tracy, Clark Gable and Jimmy Stewart in classics like Tortilla Flat (1942), White Cargo (1942), Cecil B. DeMille's Samson and Delilah (1949) and The Female Animal (1957).

Selected Works

  • Algiers (1938)
  • Samson and Delilah (1949)
  • The Female Animal (1957)

Inventor

  • Secret Communication System (US Patent 2,292,387)
  • Frequency-hopping spread spectrum
